ilms in their sociohistorical context to reposition the director as a trenchant satirist and social critic of postmodern America, depicted as a lonely wasteland of fraudulent spectacle, exploitative social relations, and unfulfilled solitaries in search of elusive community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857840uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/niem1762640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231850865423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231850865/original  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles